- The financial period "201802" likely refers to the second month of the financial year 2018.;
- The access types "view" and "download" indicate whether the user simply viewed the data or downloaded it for further use.

- 'Year-over-year' (YoY) refers to a comparison of a financial metric between the same period in consecutive years;
- 'Liability' in financial terms refers to the debts or obligations a company owes;
- 'Industry average' is the mean value of a metric across all companies within the same industry.

- 'YOYLiability' refers to the year-over-year change in liability;
- The query ranks periods by the percentage increase in liability;
- The highest YOY change is selected for each company.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM financial_data
WHERE period_id = (SELECT period_id FROM financial_periods WHERE period_name = '201801');

